class.name: CATSAXException
class.abstract: Class to encapsulate a general SAX error or warning.

class.name: CATSAXIOException
class.abstract: Class to encapsulates an IO error in the context of a SAX parser.

class.name: CATSAXNotRecognizedException
class.abstract: Class for errors related to an unrecognized operation.

class.name: CATSAXNotSupportedException
class.abstract: Class for errors related to an unsupported operation.

class.name: CATSAXParseException
class.abstract: Class to encapsulate an XML parse error or warning.

class.name: CATSAXXMLReaderOptions
class.abstract: Class to group constants which correspond to the standard SAX2 features and properties.

data.name: DeclHandlerProperty
data.abstract: Property to specify a decl handler for decl events generated by a <tt>CATIXMLSAXReader</tt>.

data.name: ExternalGeneralEntitiesFeature
data.abstract: Reports whether this parser processes external general entities; always true if validating.

data.name: ExternalParameterEntitiesFeature
data.abstract: Reports whether this parser processes external parameter entities; always true if validating.

data.name: LexicalHandlerProperty
data.abstract: Property to specify a lexical handler for lexical events generated by a <tt>CATIXMLSAXReader</tt>.

data.name: NamespacePrefixFeature
data.abstract: Feature to add namespace definition attributes to <tt>CATISAXAttributes</tt>.

data.name: NamespacesFeature
data.abstract: Feature to activate namespace support in <tt>CATISAXAttributes</tt>.

class.name: CATXMLPPException
class.abstract: Class to encapsulate errors raised by the CATIXMLPPWriter interface.

class.name: CATXMLPPMemoryBuffer
class.abstract: Class to implement a variable size memory buffer to store XML content generated in memory.

method.name: GetBuffer
method.abstract: Returns a pointer to the internal byte array of the memory buffer.

method.name: Write
method.abstract: Asks the memory buffer to store the supplied byte array.

function.name: CreateCATIXMLDOMDocumentBuilder
function.abstract: Returns the root object which corresponds to a specific DOM implementation.

function.name: CreateCATIXMLPPFactory
function.abstract: Returns the root object which corresponds to a specific implementation of the XML pull parser API.

function.name: CreateCATIXMLSAX2Factory
function.abstract: Returns the root object which corresponds to a specific SAX implementation.

function.name: DetectCATIXMLDOMDocumentBuilder
function.abstract: Examines the DOM implementations available on the host.

function.name: DetectCATIXMLSAXFactory
function.abstract: Examines the SAX implementations available on the host.

class.name: CATIDOMAttr
class.abstract: Interface that refers to an attribute of an XML element.

method.name: GetName
method.abstract: Retrieves the name of this attribute.

method.name: GetOwnerElement
method.abstract: Retrieves the CATIDOMElement node this attribute is attached.

method.name: GetSpecified
method.abstract: Returns wether the attribute's value was specified or not.

method.name: GetValue
method.abstract: Retrieves the value of the attribute.

method.name: SetValue
method.abstract: Sets the value of the attribute.

class.name: CATIDOMCDATASection
class.abstract: Interface referring to the data from an XML CDATA section.

class.name: CATIDOMCharacterData
class.abstract: Interface extending <tt>CATIDOMNode</tt> with a set of methods for accessing character data in the DOM.

method.name: AppendData
method.abstract: Appends the string to the end of the character data of the node.

method.name: DeleteData
method.abstract: Removes a range of characters from the node.

method.name: GetData
method.abstract: Retrieves the character data of the node that implements this interface.

method.name: GetLength
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of characters that are available through data and the SubstringData method below.

method.name: InsertData
method.abstract: Inserts a string at the specified character offset.

method.name: ReplaceData
method.abstract: Replaces the characters starting at the specified character offset with the specified string.

method.name: SetData
method.abstract: Sets the character data of the node that implements this interface.

method.name: SubstringData
method.abstract: Extracts a range of data from the node.

class.name: CATIDOMComment
class.abstract: Interface representing XML comment nodes in the DOM.

class.name: CATIDOMDocument
class.abstract: Interface to refer to XML Document nodes in the DOM.

method.name: CreateAttribute
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMAttr</tt> of the given name.

method.name: CreateAttributeNS
method.abstract: Creates an attribute of the given qualified name and namespace URI.

method.name: CreateCDATASection
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMCDATASection</tt> node whose value is the specified string.

method.name: CreateComment
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMComment</tt> node given the specified string.

method.name: CreateDocumentFragment
method.abstract: Creates an empty <tt>CATIDOMDocumentFragment</tt> object.

method.name: CreateElement
method.abstract: Creates an element of the type specified.

method.name: CreateElementNS
method.abstract: Creates an element of the given qualified name and namespace URI.

method.name: CreateEntityReference
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMEntityReference</tt> object.

method.name: CreateProcessingInstruction
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMProcessingInstruction</tt> node given the specified name and data strings.

method.name: CreateTextNode
method.abstract: Creates a <tt>CATIDOMText</tt> node given the specified string.

method.name: GetDocType
method.abstract: Retrieves the Document Type Declaration associated with this document.

method.name: GetDocumentElement
method.abstract: Retrieves a reference to the root element of the document.

method.name: GetElementById
method.abstract: Retrieves the <tt>CATIDOMElement</tt> whose ID is given by <tt>iElementId</tt>.

method.name: GetElementsByTagName
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMNodeList</tt> of all the elements with a given tag name.

method.name: GetElementsByTagNameNS
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMNodeList</tt> of all the <tt>CATIDOMElement</tt>s with a given local name and namespace URI.

method.name: GetImplementation
method.abstract: Return the <tt>CATIDOMImplementation</tt> object that handles this document.

method.name: ImportNode
method.abstract: Imports a copy of a node from another document into this document.

class.name: CATIDOMDocumentFragment
class.abstract: Interface representing a "lightweight" or "minimal" CATIDOMDocument object.

class.name: CATIDOMDocumentTraversal
class.abstract: Interface which contains methods that create iterators and tree-walkers to traverse a node and its children in document order (depth first, pre-order traversal, which is equivalent to the order in which the start tags occur in the text representation of the document).

method.name: CreateNodeIterator
method.abstract: Creates a new <tt>CATIDOMNodeIterator</tt> over the subtree rooted at the specified node.

method.name: CreateTreeWalker
method.abstract: Creates a new <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> over the subtree rooted at the specified node.

class.name: CATIDOMDocumentType
class.abstract: Interface providing access to the list of entities and notations that are defined in the document.

method.name: GetEntities
method.abstract: Retrieves a CATIDOMNamedNodeMap containing the general entities, both external and internal, declared in the DTD.

method.name: GetInternalSubset
method.abstract: Get the internal subset as a string.

method.name: GetName
method.abstract: Retrieves the name of DTD.

method.name: GetNotations
method.abstract: Retrieves a CATIDOMNamedNodeMap containing an entry for each notation declared in a document's DTD.

method.name: GetPublicId
method.abstract: Retrieves the public identifier of the external subset.

method.name: GetSystemId
method.abstract: Get the system identifier of the external subset.

class.name: CATIDOMElement
class.abstract: Interface representing by far the vast majority of objects nodes (apart from text) that authors encounter when traversing a document.

method.name: GetAttribute
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute value by name.

method.name: GetAttributeNS
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute value by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: GetAttributeNode
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMAttr</tt> node by name.

method.name: GetAttributeNodeNS
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMAttr</tt> node by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: GetElementsByTagName
method.abstract: Returns a <tt>CATIDOMNodeList</tt> of all descendant elements with a given tag name.

method.name: GetElementsByTagNameNS
method.abstract: Returns a <tt>CATIDOMNodeList</tt> of all the <tt>CATIDOMElement</tt>s with a given local name and namespace URI in the order in which they would be encountered in a preorder traversal of the <tt>CATIDOMDocument</tt> tree, starting from this node.

method.name: GetTagName
method.abstract: Retrieves the name of the element.

method.name: HasAttribute
method.abstract: Returns <tt>TRUE</tt> when an attribute with a given name is specified on this element or has a default value, <tt>FALSE</tt> otherwise.

method.name: HasAttributeNS
RemoveAttribute
method.abstract: Removes an attribute by name.

method.name: RemoveAttributeNS
method.abstract: Removes an attribute by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: RemoveAttributeNode
method.abstract: Removes the specified attribute.

method.name: SetAttribute
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute.

method.name: SetAttributeNS
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute.

method.name: SetAttributeNode
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute.

method.name: SetAttributeNodeNS
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute.

class.name: CATIDOMEntity
class.abstract: Interface to represent an entity, either parsed or unparsed, in an XML document.

method.name: GetNotationName
method.abstract: For unparsed entities, retrives the name of the notation for the entity.

method.name: GetPublicId
method.abstract: Retrives the public identifier associated with the entity, if specified.

method.name: GetSystemId
method.abstract: Retrives the system identifier associated with the entity, if specified.

class.name: CATIDOMEntityReference
class.abstract: Interface for object which may be inserted into the structure model when an entity reference is in the source document, or when the user wishes to insert an entity reference.

class.name: CATIDOMImplementation
class.abstract: Interface providing a number of methods for performing operations that are independent of any particular instance of the document object model.

method.name: CreateDocument
method.abstract: Creates an XML CATIDOMDocument object of the specified type with its document element.

method.name: CreateDocumentType
method.abstract: Creates an empty CATIDOMDocumentType node.

method.name: HasFeature
method.abstract: Tests if the DOM implementation implements a specific feature.

class.name: CATIDOMNamedNodeMap
class.abstract: Interface used to represent collections of nodes that can be accessed by name.

method.name: GetLength
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of nodes in this map.

method.name: GetNamedItem
method.abstract: Retrieves a node specified by name.

method.name: GetNamedItemNS
method.abstract: Retrieves a node specified by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: Item
method.abstract: Retrieves the indexth item in the map.

method.name: RemoveNamedItem
method.abstract: Removes a node specified by name.

method.name: RemoveNamedItemNS
method.abstract: Removes a node specified by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: SetNamedItem
method.abstract: Adds a node using its nodeName attribute.

method.name: SetNamedItemNS
method.abstract: Adds a node using its namespace URI and local name.

class.name: CATIDOMNode
class.abstract: Interface used as the primary datatype for the entire Document Object Model.

method.name: AppendChild
method.abstract: Adds the node <tt>iNewChild</tt> to the end of the list of children of this node.

method.name: CloneNode
method.abstract: Returns a duplicate of this node.

method.name: GetAttributes
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMNamedNodeMap</tt> containing the attributes of this node.

method.name: GetChildNodes
method.abstract: Retrieves a <tt>CATIDOMNodeList</tt> that contains all children of this node.

method.name: GetFirstChild
method.abstract: Retrieves the first child of this node.

method.name: GetLastChild
method.abstract: Retrieves the last child of this node.

method.name: GetLocalName
method.abstract: Retrieves the local part of the qualified name of this node.

method.name: GetNamespaceURI
method.abstract: Retrieves the namespace URI of this node, or an empty <tt>CATUnicodeString</tt> if it is unspecified.

method.name: GetNextSibling
method.abstract: Retrieves node immediately following this node.

method.name: GetNodeName
method.abstract: Retrieves the name of this node, depending on its type.

method.name: GetNodeType
method.abstract: Retrieves the enum value representing the type of the underlying object.

method.name: GetNodeValue
method.abstract: Retrieves the value of this node, depending on its type.

method.name: GetOwnerDocument
method.abstract: Retrieves the <tt>CATIDOMDocument</tt> object associated with this node.

method.name: GetParentNode
method.abstract: Retrieves the parent of this node.

method.name: GetPrefix
method.abstract: Retrieves the namespace prefix of this node, or an empty <tt>CATUnicodeString</tt> if it is unspecified.

method.name: GetPreviousSibling
method.abstract: Retrieves node immediately preceding this node.

method.name: HasAttributes
method.abstract: Returns whether this node (if it is an element) has any attributes.

method.name: HasChildNodes
method.abstract: Returns whether this node has any children.

method.name: InsertBefore
method.abstract: Inserts the node <tt>iNewChild</tt> before the existing child node <tt>iRefChild</tt>.

method.name: IsSupported
method.abstract: Tests whether the DOM implementation implements a specific feature and that feature is supported by this node.

method.name: Normalize
method.abstract: Puts all <tt>CATIDOMText</tt> nodes in the full depth of the sub-tree underneath this <tt>CATIDOMNode</tt>, including attribute nodes, into a "normal" form.

method.name: RemoveChild
method.abstract: Removes the child node indicated by <tt>iOldChild</tt> from the list of children.

method.name: ReplaceChild
method.abstract: Replaces the child node <tt>iOldChild</tt> with <tt>iNewChild</tt> in the list of children.

method.name: SetNodeValue
method.abstract: Sets the value of the node.

method.name: SetPrefix
method.abstract: Sets the namespace prefix of this node.

class.name: CATIDOMNodeFilter
class.abstract: Interface for filters objects that know how to "filter out" nodes.

method.name: AcceptNode
method.abstract: Tests whether a specified node is visible in the logical view of a <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> or <tt>CATIDOMNodeIterator</tt>.

class.name: CATIDOMNodeIterator
class.abstract: Interface used to step through a set of nodes.

method.name: Detach
method.abstract: Detaches the <tt>CATIDOMNodeIterator</tt> from the set which it iterated over, releasing any computational resources and placing the iterator in the INVALID state.

method.name: GetExpandEntityReferences
method.abstract: Retrieves the flag which determines whether the children of entity reference nodes are visible to the iterator.

method.name: GetFilter
method.abstract: Retrieves the <tt>CATIDOMNodeFilter</tt> used to screen nodes.

method.name: GetRoot
method.abstract: Retrieves the root node of the <tt>CATIDOMNodeIterator</tt>, as specified when it was created.

method.name: GetWhatToShow
method.abstract: Retrieves which node types are presented via the iterator.

method.name: NextNode
method.abstract: Retrieves the next node in the set and advances the position of the iterator in the set.

method.name: PreviousNode
method.abstract: Retrieves the previous node in the set and moves the position of the <tt>CATIDOMNodeIterator</tt> backwards in the set.

class.name: CATIDOMNodeList
class.abstract: Interface providing the abstraction of an ordered collection of nodes.

method.name: GetLength
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of nodes in the list.

method.name: Item
method.abstract: Retrieves the indexth item in the collection.

class.name: CATIDOMNotation
class.abstract: Interface to represent a notation declared in the DTD.

method.name: GetPublicId
method.abstract: Retrieves the public identifier of this notation.

method.name: GetSystemId
method.abstract: Retrieves the system identifier of this notation.

class.name: CATIDOMProcessingInstruction
class.abstract: Interface to represent a "processing instruction", used in XML as a way to keep processor-specific information in the text of the document.

method.name: GetData
method.abstract: Retrieves the content of this processing instruction.

method.name: GetTarget
method.abstract: Retrieves the target of this processing instruction.

method.name: SetData
method.abstract: Sets the content of this processing instruction.

class.name: CATIDOMText
class.abstract: Interface representing the textual content (termed character data in XML) of a CATIDOMElement or CATIDOMAttr.

method.name: SplitText
method.abstract: Breaks this node into two nodes at the specified iOffset, keeping both in the tree as siblings.

class.name: CATIDOMTreeWalker
class.abstract: Interface used to navigate a document tree or subtree using the view of the document defined by their <tt>GetWhatToShow</tt> flags and filter (if any).

method.name: FirstChild
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the first visible child of the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: GetCurrentNode
method.abstract: Retrieves the node at which the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> is currently positioned.

method.name: GetExpandEntityReferences
method.abstract: Retrieves the flag which determines whether the children of entity reference nodes are visible to the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt>.

method.name: GetFilter
method.abstract: Retrieves the filter used to screen nodes.

method.name: GetRoot
method.abstract: Retrieves the root node of the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt>, as specified when it was created.

method.name: GetWhatToShow
method.abstract: Retrieves the attribute which determines which node types are presented via the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt>.

method.name: LastChild
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the last visible child of the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: NextNode
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the next visible node in document order relative to the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: NextSibling
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the next sibling of the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: ParentNode
method.abstract: Moves to and returns the closest visible ancestor node of the current node.

method.name: PreviousNode
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the previous visible node in document order relative to the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: PreviousSibling
method.abstract: Moves the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> to the previous sibling of the current node, and returns the new node.

method.name: SetCurrentNode
method.abstract: Sets the node at which the <tt>CATIDOMTreeWalker</tt> is to be currently positioned.

class.name: CATISAXAttributes
class.abstract: Interface for a list of XML attributes.

method.name: GetIndex
method.abstract: Retrieves the index of an attribute by XML 1·0 qualified name.

method.name: GetIndex
method.abstract: Retrieves the index of an attribute by Namespace name.

method.name: GetLength
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of attributes in this list.

method.name: GetLocalName
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute's XML 1·0 local name by index.

method.name: GetQName
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute's XML 1·0 qualified name by index.

method.name: GetType
method.abstract: Retrieves the type of an attribute (by position).

method.name: GetType
method.abstract: Retrieves the type of an attribute (by XML 1·0 qualified name).

method.name: GetType
method.abstract: Retrieves the type of an attribute (by Namespace name).

method.name: GetURI
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute's Namespace URI by index.

method.name: GetValue
method.abstract: Retrieves the value of an attribute (by position).

method.name: GetValue
method.abstract: Retrieves the value of an attribute (by XML 1·0 qualified name).

method.name: GetValue
method.abstract: Retrieves the value of an attribute (by Namespace name).

class.name: CATISAXContentHandler
class.abstract: Interface to receive notification of the logical content of a document.

method.name: Characters
method.abstract: Receives notification of character data.

method.name: EndDocument
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of a document.

method.name: EndElement
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of an element.

method.name: EndPrefixMapping
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of the scope of a prefix-URI Namespace mapping.

method.name: IgnorableWhiteSpace
method.abstract: Receives notification of ignorable whitespace in element content.

method.name: ProcessingInstruction
method.abstract: Receives notification of a processing instruction.

method.name: SetDocumentLocator
method.abstract: Receives an object for locating the origin of SAX content events.

method.name: SkippedEntity
method.abstract: Receives notification of a skipped entity.

method.name: StartDocument
method.abstract: Receives notification of the beginning of a document.

method.name: StartElement
method.abstract: Receives notification of the beginning of an element.

method.name: StartPrefixMapping
method.abstract: Receives notification of the beginning of the scope of a prefix-URI Namespace mapping.

class.name: CATISAXDTDHandler
class.abstract: Interface to receive notification of basic DTD-related events.

method.name: NotationDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of a notation declaration event.

method.name: UnparsedEntityDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of an unparsed entity declaration event.

class.name: CATISAXDeclHandler
class.abstract: Interface to receive notification of DTD declaration events.

method.name: AttributeDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of an attribute type declaration.

method.name: ElementDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of an element type declaration.

method.name: ExternalEntityDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of an external entity declaration.

method.name: InternalEntityDecl
method.abstract: Receives notification of an internal entity declaration.

class.name: CATISAXEntityResolver
class.abstract: Interface for resolving entities.

method.name: ResolveEntity
method.abstract: Allows the application to resolve external entities.

class.name: CATISAXErrorHandler
class.abstract: Interface for SAX error handlers.

method.name: Error
method.abstract: Receives notification of a recoverable error.

method.name: FatalError
method.abstract: Receives notification of a non-recoverable error.

method.name: Warning
method.abstract: Receives notification of a warning.

class.name: CATISAXInputSource
class.abstract: Interface to represent a single input source for an XML entity.

method.name: GetEncoding
method.abstract: Retrieves the name of the encoding that is to be forced.

method.name: GetPublicId
method.abstract: Retrieves the public identifier for this input source.

method.name: GetSystemId
method.abstract: Retrieves the system identifier for this input source.

method.name: SetEncoding
method.abstract: Sets the encoding which will be required for use with the XML text read via a stream opened by this input source.

method.name: SetPublicId
method.abstract: Sets the public identifier for this input source.

method.name: SetSystemId
method.abstract: Sets the system identifier for this input source.

class.name: CATISAXLexicalHandler
class.abstract: Interface to receive notification of lexical events.

method.name: Comment
method.abstract: Receives notification of an XML comment anywhere in the document.

method.name: EndCDATA
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of a <tt>CDATA</tt> section.

method.name: EndDTD
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of DTD declarations.

method.name: EndEntity
method.abstract: Receives notification of the end of an entity.

method.name: StartCDATA
method.abstract: Receives notification of the start of a <tt>CDATA</tt> section.

method.name: StartDTD
